OL,3,CMan avoids prison after dog bite
OL,4,Clinked to pensioner's death
OL,6,FA man from Workington has avoided
OL,7,Fprison after his Patterdale terrier
OL,8,Fbit an elderly neighbour who died
OL,9,Fweeks later after developing a blood
OL,10,Finfection linked to the bite.
OL,12,FMartin Hawley, 58, met 89-year-old
OL,13,FJoseph James outside their Warwick
OL,14,FPlace terraced homes on the evening of
OL,15,F21 October 2022.
OL,17,FAs Hawley opened his door and Mr James
OL,18,Fstood outside his address, Hawley's
OL,19,Fterrier, Annie, ran from the house and
OL,20,Flatched on to the pensioner's hand,
OL,21,Fpulling him to the floor.
