OL,3,CMan avoids prison after dog bite
OL,4,Clinked to pensioner's death
OL,6,FHawley, 58, called an ambulance which
OL,7,Ftook him to hospital where he remained
OL,8,Funtil he died nearly a month later.
OL,10,FHe had bruising and swelling to the
OL,11,Fleft side of his head, a nosebleed and
OL,12,Fpartial amputation of one of his
OL,13,Ffingertips.
OL,15,FA pathologist concluded that Mr James'
OL,16,Fhead injury was neither life-
OL,17,Fthreatening nor life-changing.
OL,19,FAfter a week in hospital, Mr James
OL,20,Fturned 90. He developed a fever and a
OL,21,Fweek later was diagnosed with sepsis.
