OL,4,Clinked to pensioner's death
OL,6,FA neighbour reported Mr James for
OL,7,Fusing a cane and previously tormenting
OL,8,Fthe dog, which had bitten the
OL,9,Fpensioner in the past.
OL,11,FJudge Michael Fanning accepted this
OL,12,Ftorment but told Hawley the 21 October
OL,13,Fincident could have been foreseen,
OL,14,Fadding: "These incidents should have
OL,15,Fput you on notice that you had to be
OL,16,Fcareful with Annie being around Mr
OL,17,FJames."
OL,19,FDefence lawyer Craig MacGregor
OL,20,Fconceded there were "no winners" in
OL,21,Fthe case.
