OL,3,CMan avoids prison after dog bite
OL,4,Clinked to pensioner's death
OL,6,FHe added: "The defendant, who suffers
OL,7,Ffrom depression, has been greatly
OL,8,Faffected by this.
OL,10,F"He still lives at the house. He still
OL,11,Fhas to face this every day."
OL,13,FJudge Fanning said it had been a
OL,14,F"momentary lapse" by Hawley, adding:
OL,15,F"You have demonstrated real remorse
OL,16,Fand regret. I have no doubt this will
OL,17,Flive with you forever."
OL,19,FAn 18-month prison sentence was
OL,20,Fsuspended for a year.
